ZH: 他是个打铁的，每天都在铁匠铺里工作。
EN: He is a blacksmith and works in the forge every day.

ZH: 我的父亲是打铁的，他花了很多年来磨练这门手艺。
EN: My father is a blacksmith, and he has spent many years honing his craft.

ZH: 那个打铁的创造了一个美丽的铁艺作品。
EN: The blacksmith created a beautiful ironwork piece.

ZH: 打铁的需要有很高的专业技能。
EN: Being a blacksmith requires a high level of professional skills.

ZH: 我们用的这把锤子是由一位打铁的亲手制作的。
EN: The hammer we are using was handmade by a blacksmith.

ZH: 打铁的需要有耐心和细致的工作态度。
EN: Blacksmiths need to have patience and a meticulous work attitude.

ZH: 这家铁匠铺有几个打铁的同时在工作。
EN: There are several blacksmiths working at the forge.

ZH: 打铁的常常要在火堆旁工作，所以他们的工作环境比较热。
EN: Blacksmiths often work near the fire, so their working environment tends to be hot.

ZH: 打铁的可以根据客户的要求定制不同的铁艺作品。
EN: Blacksmiths can customize different ironwork pieces based on customer requirements.

ZH: 打铁的将铁块加热变软，然后锤打成所需形状。
EN: Blacksmiths heat the iron pieces to soften them and then hammer them into the desired shape.

ZH: 打铁的需要有一把锤子和铁制品加热工具。
EN: Blacksmiths need a hammer and tools for heating iron products.

ZH: 这位打铁的已经创建了许多精美的艺术作品。
EN: This blacksmith has created many exquisite art pieces.

ZH: 这位打铁的有强壮的身体，因为他每天都要锤打铁块。
EN: This blacksmith has a strong physique because he hammers iron pieces every day.

ZH: 打铁的技艺需要长时间的练习和磨砺。
EN: The skill of blacksmithing requires long-term practice and honing.

ZH: 这个小村庄里没有打铁的，所以村民们不得不远行找铁匠。
EN: There is no blacksmith in this small village, so the villagers have to travel far to find one.

ZH: 打铁的嘴巴上留着黑色的痕迹，这是因为他们经常需要咀嚼焦炭。
EN: Blacksmiths often have black marks on their mouths because they frequently chew charcoal.

ZH: 我们邀请了一位打铁的来教我们如何制作铁艺作品。
EN: We invited a blacksmith to teach us how to make ironwork pieces.

ZH: 打铁的用锤子锤打铁块，使其变得更加坚固。
EN: The blacksmith hammers the iron pieces to make them stronger.

ZH: 这个小镇上最好的打铁的店铺是传统的家族经营。
EN: The best blacksmith shop in this small town is a traditional family-owned business.

ZH: 打铁的确实是一门非常精细的工艺技能。
EN: Blacksmithing is indeed a very delicate craft skill.
